amendatorysection.para:
(a) The health, safety,
and welfare of the public are inadequately addressed by the present scope
of practice or limitations on the scope of practice;

(b) Enactment of the proposed
change in scope of practice would benefit the health, safety, or welfare of
the public;

(c) The proposed
change in scope of practice does not create a significant new danger to the
health, safety, or welfare of the public;

(d) The current education and training
for the health profession adequately prepares practitioners to perform the
new skill or service;
